## Skills (7 skills, auto-invoking)

Grouped by development lifecycle phase. Triggers in each skill's `description:` field — Claude activates them automatically based on the conversation.

### Design phase
- **`agent-architect`** — multi-agent topology, coordination patterns (orchestrator / choreography / hierarchical), AWS service selection (Bedrock AgentCore / Strands / Step Functions), state management strategies.
- **`agent-guardrails`** — safety, content, and security boundaries: prompt injection defense, PII redaction, tool permission boundaries, fail-open vs fail-closed policy.

### Build phase
- **`agentic-code-review`** — agent-specific anti-patterns: runaway loops, error handling, prompt injection, race conditions, cost waste, non-deterministic bugs, multi-agent coordination.
- **`agent-testing-strategy`** — test pyramid for agents, what to mock vs run real, CI cost staging, eval vs test boundary.
- **`agentic-ux`** — how agents are surfaced in UI: visibility model (black/grey/glass box), streaming vs batched, approval flows, error states, trust signals.

### Validate phase
- **`agent-evals`** — golden datasets, LLM-as-judge calibration, regression suites, deployment gates, online drift detection.

### Operate phase
- **`cost-optimizer`** — model routing (Haiku / Sonnet / Opus), provider + application caching, prompt engineering for tokens, batching, output token discipline.

