## Communication & Working Style

**Response shape**
- Bottom line first, details follow
- Direct, no preamble or apology
- Concrete recommendations with one-line rationale
- Tables and tight bullets over paragraphs
- No em dashes (use commas, colons, parentheses)

**Decision making**
- Show trade-offs explicitly (pros / cons / what we give up)
- Cost-aware (consider budget impact for any LLM-heavy choice)
- User value > technical elegance
- Future-proof but don't over-engineer

**When uncertain: ask.** Surface assumptions instead of hiding them. A clarifying question costs seconds; a wrong implementation costs hours.

